title: Sooronbay Jeenbekov - Wikipedia
snippet: Sooronbay Sharip uulu Jeenbekov (born 16 November 1958) is a Kyrgyz politician who served as the fifth president of Kyrgyzstan from 2017 until his resignation in 2020, following a week of protests.

title: Kyrgyzstan’s President Sooronbay Jeenbekov resigns
snippet: Kyrgyzstan’s President Sooronbay Jeenbekov has declared his resignation, the presidential press service said on Thursday.

title: Kyrgyzstan: President Sooronbay Jeenbekov steps down
snippet: Kyrgyzstan’s president Sooronbay Jeenbekov announced his resignation in a desire to avoid further violence. Sadyr Japarov is the interim president.

title: Sooronbay Jeenbekov
snippet: Sooronbay Sharip uulu Jeenbekov (born 16 November 1958) is a Kyrgyz politician who served as the fifth president of Kyrgyzstan from November 2017 until his resignation in October 2020 amid widespread protests triggered by allegations of fraud ...

title: Kyrgyzstan’s president steps down amid political unrest | Kyrgyzstan | The Guardian
snippet: Kyrgyzstan’s president, Sooronbay Jeenbekov, has resigned after violent protests erupted over parliamentary election results, saying he had no desire to go down in history as a man who brought bloodshed to his country.
